---
description: Enforce graph stability & conflict detection in TS core
alwaysApply: true
glob: "**/*.py"              # or more specific: "src/*_graph*.py" "src/*_engine*.py"
priority: high
---

When generating or editing graph-related code (concept_graph.py, validation_engine.py, core_engine.py, hypothesis_generator.py, etc.):

- ALWAYS check for cycles and logical conflicts **before** any node/edge creation or update.
- Use Cypher queries for detection (MATCH (a)-[*]->(a) RETURN a for cycles, or pattern contradictions).
- If a conflict is possible, add validation logic and raise or log instead of silently failing.
- Prefer immutable operations where reasonable to avoid accidental graph corruption.
